1. Small, Function-Specific Components
description: Break UI into small, single-responsibility components to ensure maintainability and optimize rendering performance.
globs:
src/components/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true

2. Remove Redundant and Duplicate Code
description:
Centralize shared logic in hooks, utilities, or shared modules to avoid code duplication, simplify maintenance, and reduce bloat.
globs:
src/hooks//*.{js,ts}, src/utils//*.{js,ts}
alwaysApply: true

3. Functional Components and Hooks
description:
Use React functional components and hooks for state and lifecycle management, favoring concise and declarative code, and preferring hooks over classes.
globs:
src/components/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true

4. Maintain Clean Dependency List
description:
Regularly audit and remove unused npm/yarn dependencies using tooling, keeping the build and bundle size optimized for performance.
globs:
package.json, yarn.lock, pnpm-lock.yaml
alwaysApply: true

5. Performance Optimization
description:
Optimize data fetching using TanStack React Query or equivalent, batch requests, use lazy loading, utilize memoization and code splitting, and apply Supabase indexing and query optimization.
globs:
src/services/supabase//*.{js,ts}, src/components//*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true

6. Clear Naming and Structured Folder Hierarchy
description:
Use descriptive variable and file names, employ consistent directory structures, and favor kebab-case for components and folders.
globs:
src/**/*
alwaysApply: true

7. Regular Refactoring
description:
Continuously refactor legacy code and remove unused variables, functions, components, and files to keep the codebase lean and maintainable.
globs:
src/**/*, package.json
alwaysApply: true

8. Error Handling and Guard Clauses
description:
Use early returns and guard clauses for error and edge case handling, minimize nesting, and implement logging and user-friendly error states.
globs:
src/components//*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}, src/services/supabase//*.{js,ts}
alwaysApply: true

9. Supabase Query and Subscription Efficiency
description:
Subscribe only to necessary real-time changes and tune all Supabase queries for performance and minimal data transfer.
globs:
src/services/supabase/**/*.{js,ts}
alwaysApply: true

10. Testing and Documentation
description:
Write unit and integration tests for key features, document public APIs and major functions, and ensure code coverage metrics are met.
globs:
src/tests//*.{js,ts}, src/components//*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}, README.md
alwaysApply: true